            <thetext>I know this is probably themable, since the &quot;Classic&quot; theme don&#39;t include them, but it really shouldn&#39;t be the case in the modern theme either. 

All GUI toolkits I know (Gtk, Swt, Cocoa), and probably others don&#39;t include borders. This should be either an option (if the developer wants borders, he should set it explicitly) or not the case at all (to have the border you&#39;d have to add an extra widget containing the splitpane).</thetext>
